claim.claim-text:
9. A battery charging cable assembly, comprising:
a conduit segment containing a portion of a transmission cable, the conduit segment having an inner diameter that is greater than an outer diameter of the transmission cable;
a major looping pulley rotatably looped by the transmission cable;
a lower pulley rotatably looped by the transmission cable;
a mass augmentation coupled to the lower pulley to pull the lower pulley;
wherein the transmission cable is operable to aid in the retraction of the transmission cable from the conduit segment, with the mass augmentation configured to overcome the sliding friction of the transmission cable contained in the conduit segment and major looping and lower pulley rotation friction.

15. A battery charging cable assembly comprising:
a conduit segment configured to expel a transmission cable;
wherein the transmission cable is air-cooled within a volume between the transmission cable and the conduit segment.
